# Pasa Rate PH — Core Conventions

## Program registry is the single source of truth
- Supported board exams live ONLY in `src/lib/programs.ts` (and its Python mirror
  `scraper/programs.py` + `supabase/seed/seed.sql`).
- NEVER hardcode exam-code lists elsewhere. Import from the registry.
- To add a program: add a registry entry in all three places, run the seed, scrape.

## Supabase access
- Public reads: `getServerClient()` / `getBrowserClient()` (anon key, RLS-limited).
- Trusted writes (ETL/admin only): `getServiceClient()` (service role, server-only).
- Never import `getServiceClient` or `src/lib/admin.ts` into client components.
- Always guard pages with `isSupabaseConfigured()` so the app degrades gracefully
  before keys are set.

## Data integrity
- All ETL writes are idempotent upserts on the UNIQUE keys in
  `supabase/migrations/0001_init.sql`. Keep them that way.
- Validate and parse all API query params; respond with `apiError(...)` from
  `src/lib/http.ts`. Wrap public handlers in `withRateLimit(...)`.

## Secrets
- Keys come from env only (`.env.local` / Vercel). Never commit `.env`.
- `.env.example` documents every required variable.
